{
  "texts": [
    "Although current research mainly focuses on single-agent tool usage or short-term scenarios, tool-using metrics can be effectively used to measure the self-organization and cooperation abilities of LLMs in multi-agent scenarios.",
    "Tool-RoCo fills this gap by embedding tool usage in cooperation and treating other agents as tools, thus introducing metrics such as selforganization and cooperation-tool ratio.",
    "These metrics enable Tool-RoCo to systematically evaluate organization capability of LLM in long horizontal tasks.",
    "Tool-RoCo is an LLM-based long-term multi-agent benchmark built upon the three tasks in the RoCo environment (Mandi, Jain, and Song 2024): CABINET, PACK, and SORT (Left side of Fig. 2).",
    "Each task is defined as follows:"
  ]
}